# SDOC — Implementation Status @sdoc-impl-status
{
    # Meta @meta
    {
        type: doc

        status: active

        sdoc-version: 0.2
    }

    # About @about
    {
        Implementation status for the SDOC project. Tracks what is completed, what is in progress, and what is next. Read this first when starting a new task.
    }

    # Current State @current-state
    {
        SDOC v0.2.8 is the current release. The parser, HTML renderer, slide renderer, and VS Code extension are stable and published to both npm and the VS Code Marketplace (auto-updates enabled). The format supports scope types, data blocks, comment scopes, table formulas, email auto-detection, collapsible scopes in all HTML output, and a full inline formatting suite. Issues are open on github/markup and github-linguist for GitHub rendering and language recognition.

        The spec is expected to evolve. The core principle of explicit brace scoping is stable. Everything else is open to change, with the constraint that existing documents must remain valid or be mechanically migrateable ([R10](requirements.sdoc#r10)).
    }

    # Completed @completed
    {
        The parser, renderer, and tooling are feature-complete for v0.2. See `specification.sdoc` for the full feature set. Key milestones:

        {[.]
            - v0.2.0 — scope types, data blocks, comment scopes, table width/alignment, key:value meta, line comments, K&R brace style, braceless scopes, implicit root scope
            - v0.2.4 — escaped pipes in table cells
            - v0.2.5 — auto-detected email addresses, file watcher for external preview writes
            - v0.2.6 — table formulas (=SUM, =AVG, =COUNT, arithmetic, A1 references, circular reference detection)
            - v0.2.7 — VS Code Marketplace publishing (entropicwarrior-msenfin.vscode-sdoc), progressive disclosure API documented
            - v0.2.8 — collapsible scopes and copy-to-clipboard in all standalone HTML output
            - v0.2.12 — citations (\`[@key]\` inline references, \`{[citations]\` definition blocks, auto-numbering by order of first appearance, back-links, validation)
        }

        # GitHub Adoption
        {
            - [x] Issue opened on github/markup for SDOC rendering support (github/markup#2030)
            - [x] Issue opened on github-linguist for .sdoc language recognition (github-linguist/linguist#7838)
            - [x] sdoc2html CLI translator built as contribution artifact for github/markup
            - [x] llms.txt at repo root for AI agent discovery
        }
    }

    # In Progress @in-progress
    {
        - [ ] Awaiting feedback on github/markup issue (#2030) and github-linguist issue (#7838)
        - [ ] Growing .sdoc file count on GitHub toward linguist recognition threshold (~200 unique repos)
    }

    # Next Up @next-up
    {
        These are agreed tasks ready to be picked up, not a full backlog.

        # Parser Improvements
        {
            - [ ] Enforce single root scope (grammar says `document = scope` but parser allows multiple top-level scopes). Parser should warn on violation. See [C1](requirements.sdoc#c1).
            - [ ] Decouple rendering from AST. Current renderer functions are HTML-centric. Need format-neutral AST with separate renderer modules. See [C2](requirements.sdoc#c2).
        }

        # Extension Improvements
        {
            - [ ] Preview should auto-update when switching active editor tabs (currently requires re-running the preview command)
        }

        # Spec Additions
        {
            - [ ] Document metadata ([S2](suggestions.sdoc#s2)) -- key:value meta is implemented; remaining work is defining canonical well-known keys and exposing `meta.properties` to downstream consumers
        }

        # Export Pipeline
        {
            - [ ] SDOC to Google Docs export (for collaboration with non-technical people)
            - [ ] SDOC to DOCX export
            - [ ] Simple Google Docs / DOCX to SDOC import (for round-tripping simple documents)
        }
    }
}
